this seem dangerous to me. Your overload will take priority over conversion.

```c++
#include <cstdio>
#include <utility>

template<class T>
long foo(T&& t) { puts(__PRETTY_FUNCTION__); return std::forward<T>(t); }
long foo(long t) { puts(__PRETTY_FUNCTION__); return t;}
int main() {
  foo(1);
  foo(1L);
  return 0;
}
```
outputs
```
long foo(T &&) [T = int]
long foo(long
